               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420103-name-439" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420103-name-439" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420103-name-439" type="surname" value="CAVE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420103-name-439" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS CAVE</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Aldersgate-street. On Sunday evening, the 19th of December, at six o'clock, I was in Beech-street, Barbican—I felt a slight pull at my pocket—I turned, and saw my handkerchief on the ground, and the prisoner close at my heels—no one else was within twenty or thirty yards of me—no one could have taken it but him—I said to him, "You rascal," and be immediately ran off, and I pursued him—this is my handkerchief—it is nearly new—he was in the act of throwing it down, as I turned—I lost sight of him—I have no doubt about his being the man.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
